        "text": "—Better, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "which putteth,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the verb being in the present tense, and referring to what was then passing after Titus’s return from Corinth.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The same earnest care.—There is no direct comparison, but what he means is the same care as his own. Titus had shown himself a true son of his spiritual father (Titus 1:1).",
        "children": [
          {
