  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 8:16-22",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Corinthians 8:16-22",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But thanks be to God ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— But while I speak of this collection which I am desirous of promoting, I would express my gratitude to God, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "who put the same earnest care ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Which I have; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "into the heart of Titus for you ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Namely, to promote this work among you. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For he accepted the exhortation ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Complied with my desire to promote and perfect this work; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "being forward ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— To undertake it; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of his own accord ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Yea, before he was spoken to. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And we ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— I and Timothy; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "have sent with him the brother",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " — The ancients generally supposed this was St. Luke; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "whose praise ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— For faithfully dispensing the gospel; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "is throughout all the churches ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Macknight interprets the clause, “whose praise, on account of the gospel which he hath written, is great, throughout all the churches of Christ in these parts.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And not that only ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Not only is he so much esteemed on these accounts, but he ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was also chosen ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Ordained and appointed; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of the churches ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Whom we consulted on this occasion, particularly of Macedonia; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to travel with us ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— To accompany me to Jerusalem; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "with this grace ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— This fruit of grace, this contribution; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "which is administered, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Which I have been the instrument of procuring; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to the glory of the same Lord ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Jesus, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "declaration of your ready mind — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Your readiness to do works of charity to the saints. This is the second character of the person who was sent by the apostle with Titus to Corinth. He was chosen by the churches of Macedonia to accompany Paul to Jerusalem, to witness his delivering their gift. This character, likewise, agrees very well to Luke. For having resided long at Philippi, he was well known to the Macedonian churches, who, by making him their messenger to Judea, showed their great respect for him. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Avoiding this ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Taking care of this; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that no man should blame us ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Charge me with any undue partial dealing, or as being unfaithful; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in this abundance ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— This large collection, the management of which is intrusted with us. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Providing for honest, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or honourable ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "things, not only in the sight of the Lord ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— To whom it is and ought to be our first and chief care to approve ourselves; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "but also in the sight of men ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— From whose minds I wish to remove every suspicion which might hinder my usefulness. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And we have sent with them ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, with Titus and Luke; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "our brother ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Probably Apollos; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "whom we have oftentimes proved diligent in many ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "other affairs, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "but now much more ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— In his endeavours to promote the collection among you; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "upon the great confidence, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — That is, I have sent him with them upon the great confidence which I have as to your goodness and liberality. Or, connecting the clause with the words immediately preceding, the sense is, that the brother spoken of was much more ready to come to Corinth, and active in his endeavours to forward the collection, upon the great confidence which he had in the good disposition of the Corinthians to the work.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "8:16-24 The apostle commends the brethren sent to collect their charity, that it might be known who they were, and how safely they might be trusted. It is the duty of all Christians to act prudently; to hinder, as far as we can, all unjust suspicions. It is needful, in the first place, to act uprightly in the sight of God, but things honest in the sight of men should also be attended to. A clear character, as well as a pure conscience, is requisite for usefulness. They brought glory to Christ as instruments, and had obtained honour from Christ to be counted faithful, and employed in his service. The good opinion others have of us, should be an argument with us to do well.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But thanks be to God - Paul regarded every right feeling, and every pure desire; every inclination to serve God or to benefit a fellow mortal, as the gift of God. He, therefore, ascribes the praise to him that Titus was disposed to show an interest in the welfare of the Corinthians.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The same earnest care - The earnest care here referred to was that the Corinthians might complete the collection, and finish what they had proposed. Titus was willing to undertake this, and see that it was done.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For you - For your completing the collection. Paul represents it as being done for them, or for their welfare. The poor saints in Judea indeed were to have the immediate benefit of the contribution, but it was a privilege for them to give, and Paul rejoiced that they had that privilege. A man who presents to Christians a feasible object of benevolence, and who furnishes them an opportunity of doing good to others, is doing good to them, and they should esteem it an act of kindness done to them. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "For you - For your completing the collection. Paul represents it as being done for them, or for their welfare. The poor saints in Judea indeed were to have the immediate benefit of the contribution, but it was a privilege for them to give, and Paul rejoiced that they had that privilege. A man who presents to Christians a feasible object of benevolence, and who furnishes them an opportunity of doing good to others, is doing good to them, and they should esteem it an act of kindness done to them. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "16, 17. Returning to the subject of 2Co 8:6.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for you—Translate, \"Which put the same earnest care for you into the heart of Titus,\" as was in myself. My care for you led me to \"desire\" him (2Co 8:6, 17, \"exhortation,\" the same Greek); but Titus had of himself the same care, whence he \"accepted (gladly) my exhortation\" (2Co 8:17) to go to you (2Co 8:6).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ver. 16,17. The apostle, by his exhortation, put Titus upon this employment of making at Corinth an extraordinary collection for the poor Christians that were in Judea; but it should seem, that when he did it, Titus let him know, that he was before resolved upon it: so as, though he went at the entreaty of the apostle, yet he went also of his own accord, having resolved upon the work before the apostle spoke to him of it. To let us know, that we are not sufficient of ourselves so much as to think one good thought, he gives ",
        "children": []
